    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Breast Cancer Cartoon: Reacting to the Reaction</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mary Kay Jaroff letter on response to Stan Mack's January 2 cartoon about breast cancer (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I am sorry for the letter writers who were sadly reminded that their own battles with cancer can go badly. But I too nursed my wife while she was in home hospice care last summer. The cartoon said it all, what those even under treatment hope never to find out, but the loving caregivers discover. I smiled through the tears, and I am sure Stan Mack shed them while drawing it.</p>
        <p>ANDREW MARKS  Roslyn Harbor</p>
      </block>
